Wash and dry all produce. Core and seed @bell pepper{1} and @long green pepper{1}, then
cut into small pieces. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}. Chop @cilantro{¼%ounce}.
Halve @lime{1}. Squeeze 1 TBSP juice from one half into a #small bowl{}; cut other half
into wedges.

In a #large bowl{}, mix @ground pork{20%ounce}, @Mexican spice blend{2%tablespoon},
@panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @salt{1%tsp}, and a few pinches of @pepper{}. Shape mixture
into 2-inch meatballs (you should have about 16).

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, tall-sided pan over
medium-high heat. Add meatballs and cook without disturbing until lightly browned on
bottom, about ~{2%minutes}. Using tongs, flip meatballs over and cook until lightly
browned on opposite side, about ~{2%minutes} more. Transfer to a #plate{}. Pour out any
oil in pan until only 1 TBSP is left.

Add bell pepper, green pepper, onion, a pinch of salt, and ½ tsp @smoked paprika{1%tsp}
to same pan over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned,
about ~{5%minutes}, adjusting heat as needed if veggies begin to brown too quickly.
Pour in @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce} and @water{¼%cup} and bring to a simmer.

> TIP: Add more paprika for more smoky flavor but be careful—it's spicy, too.

Add meatballs and any juices on plate to pan. Reduce heat to medium low, cover pan,
and simmer until meatballs are cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Meanwhile, microwave
@microwaveable jasmine rice{17%ounce} according to package instructions.

In a small bowl, stir together @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, reserved lime juice, and small
pinch of salt. Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with meatballs, sauce, and veggies
from pan. Drizzle with sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup}.
Garnish with cilantro. Serve with lime wedges.